    • Method Detail

      • getLabel

        public final ILabel getLabel()
        Gets the label to edit.

        This can be set to an exiting label to edit a specific one, or set to null to add a new label instead (e.g. for ILabelOwners that have no label yet).

        If this property is set to null, the properties Style, PreferredSize, LayoutParameter, and Tag are used for the newly-added label, just like with LabelEditingEventArgs.

        Setting this property implicitly also sets Handled to true.

        Returns:
        The Label.
        See Also:
        setLabel(ILabel)

      • getLayoutParameter

      • getOwner

        public final ILabelOwner getOwner()
        Gets the owner of the label.

        This property can be null if there is no owner known, e.g. if the event is raised for non-ILabelOwners. Otherwise it is initially set to the item for which the event is raised.

        Setting this property implicitly also sets Handled to true.

        Returns:
        The Owner.
        See Also:
        setOwner(ILabelOwner)

        public final boolean isHandled()
